03/12/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- Police announced on Thursday (December 2nd) the arrests of 177 people in a nationwide crackdown on an international human trafficking ring that forced women from Russia and Eastern Europe into prostitution.
Fifteen Greek nationals have been arrested, including the suspected leader of the gang.
An investigation, in co-operation with Russian authorities, is under way.
(AP, Radio Free Europe - 02/12/10)
